Police have launched an attempted murder inquiry after a vehicle was deliberately driven at a man in North Ayrshire. Attempted murder inquiry launched after car strikes man Police have launched an attempted murder inquiry after a vehicle was deliberately driven at a man in North Ayrshire.
The 30-year-old victim was struck by a car in East Road, Irvine, just before 13:00 on Saturday. 
He was taken to Crosshouse Hospital near Kilmarnock, where his condition was described as &quot;serious&quot;.
Police said inquiries were at an early stage but officers were treating the incident as attempted murder.
It is understood they are following a definite line of inquiry.
 